This kind of living hedge, which the Spaniards use both in their gardens and estates, became not only a means of security, but at the same time, an ever fertile nursery of cochineal, which, as well as a most beautiful paint, affords the Paraguayrians a medicine for strengthening the heart, creating perspiration‚ and counteracting poison3 so that it may be safely‚ and usefully mixed with vinegar, and other seasoning liquors.
